OL,3,CTeens due to be sentenced for
OL,4,Cmurdering Kayden Moy on Irvine beach
OL,6,FAnother witness said he had gone with
OL,7,FKayden to confront the teenagers, and
OL,8,Fthat as they reached the top of the
OL,9,Fdune, Turley brought out a knife and
OL,10,FStewart an extendable baton.
OL,12,FThe witness said: "Then out of nowhere
OL,13,FCole (Turley) just started running at
OL,14,Fus. I ran to the right, so did Kayden,
OL,15,FI jumped over a grass ledge, Kayden
OL,16,Fslipped and Cole leaped over and
OL,17,Fjumped on him.
OL,19,F"He had a knife and it hit. I saw one
OL,20,Fstab."
OL,26,@tD@SOU{D@AOU|D@FO]
